```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<manifest xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    package="com.madhub.facebookgroupposting">

    <!-- 
        The <application> element defines the overall characteristics of the app, 
        including its name, icon, and theme.
        This powerful configuration allows for seamless integration with Android's 
        native features and ensures a user-friendly experience.
    -->
    <application
        android:allowBackup="true"
        android:icon="@mipmap/ic_launcher"
        android:label="@string/app_name"
        android:roundIcon="@mipmap/ic_launcher_round"
        android:supportsRtl="true"
        android:theme="@style/AppTheme">

        <!-- 
            Registering the MainActivity, which serves as the primary entry point for the application. 
            This component facilitates user interaction and enables the scheduling of posts.
        -->
        <activity android:name=".MainActivity">
            <intent-filter>
                <action android:name="android.intent.action.MAIN" />
                <category android:name="android.intent.category.LAUNCHER" />
            </intent-filter>
        </activity>

        <!-- 
            Registering the AutomationService, which provides continuous background operations.
            This service enables 24/7 automation for posting management on Facebook groups, 
            enhancing social media management capabilities with minimal user intervention.
        -->
        <service
            android:name=".AutomationService"
            android:exported="false" />

    </application>

    <!-- 
        Permissions are essential for accessing device features and internet connectivity. 
        The following permissions are declared for optimal functionality:
    -->

    <!-- 
        This permission enables the app to access the internet, 
        allowing it to communicate with Facebook's API for scheduling posts.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.INTERNET" />

    <!-- 
        This permission allows the app to access network state,
        which is crucial for detecting connectivity and ensuring 
        uninterrupted posting automation.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE" />

    <!-- 
        This permission permits the app to write to external storage if needed,
        providing flexibility to manage files related to scheduled content.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />

    <!-- 
        This permission allows the app to read from external storage,
        essential for accessing media files that may be attached to scheduled posts.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />

</manifest>
```

### Explanation of Key Features:
1. **MainActivity**: This component is the user's gateway to interact with the Facebook group posting feature, allowing users to set up and manage their scheduled posts conveniently.
2. **AutomationService**: A robust service that ensures the app runs continuously in the background, executing scheduled posts with reliability and efficiency.
3. **Permissions**: The configuration includes essential permissions to leverage Android's capabilities, ensuring the app operates smoothly and fulfills its function of managing social media operations seamlessly.
